      "title": "Lead Lecturer - 3D Animation (Maya)",
      "description": "As a 3D animation lecturer, I played a vital role in educating and inspiring the next generation of digital artists and animators. I designed and delivered a curriculum that covers the full animation pipeline—from modeling, rigging, and texturing to lighting, rendering, and motion principles—using industry-standard software like Maya, Blender, or Unreal Engine. Beyond technical skills, I emphasized on storytelling, visual language, and creative problem-solving. By sharing real-world experience and staying current with evolving technologies and trends, I prepared the students for careers in film, gaming, advertising, and interactive media. As a mentor, I fostered both artistic growth and professional discipline, helping students build strong portfolios and industry readiness.",
